An African penguin at Bayworld, from where Buddy was snatched Frances might be mourning the loss of her home, children and life partner but Bayworld officials have refused to rule out the possibility of reuniting her with the love of her life Buddy. News of the theft of Buddy the African penguin went viral after he was snatched from his enclosure at the Bayworld complex in Port Elizabeth in late September. He was released into the ocean on the night of his abduction. Bayworld curator for land mammals and seabirds Cherie Lawrence said they had not given up the search for the penguin. She said that since his disappearance, Frances had been lost as her two chicks had died within a few days of their father s absence. I thought she might reunite with her friend Robin who was also born and hand-reared at Bayworld, but she has not been interested in anything. For the full story read Weekend Post, or get the complete newspaper, including comics, classifieds, crosswords and back editions in our e-Edition. &nbsp; &nbsp; Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share